Eric Bugenhagen said it but if you're doing power cleans as a regular brolifter and not an actual weightlifter athlete what you're doing is a very different movement from the Olympics guys because you're not optimized at all, for you it's a super heavy upper back focused compound

Like for the pros the technique is so perfect they practically flow under the bar and generate crazy force at the start etc. and it's less hypertrophy but as a regular tard lifter who has to horsecock the weight you'll be using a ton of upper back, getting crazy traps gains, etc.

People who read prophecies like "a blue horse will enter the city of Ra" and proceed to try to trigger it by buying a horse and painting it blue have the same logic as doctors who see a study say "glosomes are high in heart disease" and think "we need a drug that lowers glosomes"

It's like reading "never set foot in an evil place" and physically wearing stilts on your feet when you go to the brothel, just not how stuff works. You need the Leibnizian idea of seeing everything in its total context involving the entire rest of reality for it to have meaning.
